('212', '1', '2012-10-19 07:04:57', '2012-10-19 00:04:57', 'I’ve been neglecting you. But where could I even begin? I’ve taken a turn towards the taciturn – this definitely seems less funny now that it’s down in writing.  There’s just a friction to communication here. And that’s true of my Thailand writ large: I can’t talk to the other volunteers, I can’t talk to my host family, and I can’t talk to my friends back home. I feel stuck in the same purgatory that I felt when I was on the plane. I’m not here and I’m not there.', 'Foreign', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '22-revision-3', '', '', '2012-10-19 07:04:57', '2012-10-19 00:04:57', '', '22', 'http://www.weiluen.com/blog/212', '0', 'revision', '', '0'),
('210', '1', '2012-10-22 04:03:39', '2012-10-21 21:03:39', 'Things are starting to turn more normal here. But I\'m not sure what that means. Acclimation is just my euphemism for identity change. But it\'s hard to gauge how much I\'ve changed over here. I\'m marooned from all the comforts of home,&nbsp;all the creature comforts, all of my friends, all of everything that I remember. But you can\'t be backward looking here. You have to befriend the giant lizards that creep around your walls; you have to forget the giant bug swarms that fly into your house; you have to forget about the oppressive heat. It\'s hard. But you have to recognize that you yourself will change far more than you will ever be able to change the place that you live.&nbsp;Every day is a struggle. And it\'s tragic, but there is one place that I recognize my change beyond all else: my ambition. But, perhaps, that\'s just my euphemism for the far more frightening idea that my priorities have changed.\r\n\r\nHere, I\'m reminded of a pithy truth that I seem to have forgotten back home: &nbsp;self-actualization is awfully hard when you\'re struggling to stay afloat.\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.weiluen.com/blog/assets/water-world_mg_0828_v2.jpg\"><img src=\"http://www.weiluen.com/blog/assets/water-world_mg_0828_v2.jpg\" alt=\"\" title=\"water-world_mg_0828_v2\" width=\"660\" height=\"440\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-55\" /></a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.weiluen.com/blog/assets/wale-ambition-copy.jpg\"><img src=\"http://www.weiluen.com/blog/assets/wale-ambition-copy-600x600.jpg\" alt=\"\" title=\"wale-ambition-copy\" width=\"600\" height=\"600\" class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-54\" /></a>\r\n\r\n', 'Ambition', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '32-revision-21', '', '', '2012-10-22 04:03:39', '2012-10-21 21:03:39', '', '32', 'http://www.weiluen.com/blog/210', '0', 'revision', '', '0'),
('219', '1', '2012-10-26 07:00:24', '2012-10-26 00:00:24', 'Things are starting to turn a bit more normal here. But I\'m not sure what that means. I would say that I\'ve acclimated, but acclimate connotes far too positively.  And lately, Acclimation seems to be my personal euphemism for a complete and total identity change. But, in fairness, it\'s hard to gauge how much I\'ve changed while being here—who I was exists only as a sketchy outline, too transfigured by the nebulousness of time to ever identify in static slices. But I can still tell that I\'m different. I know that I\'ve been marooned from all the comforts of home, i.e., all the creature comforts, all of my friends, all of everything that I remember, for far too long to remain unaffected. Regardless, it doesn\'t matter. Here, there is no backwards; there is no backwards for a volunteer. You can\'t ever look behind because you\'re charging far too rapidly forward for the muddled image left in your wake to ever be worth consideration. What\'s left, the deceptively perfect simulacrum of home life, is never valuable enough to justify its possible incursion into your mind and its, consequently, immuring effects. No, you can\'t be backwards looking here. You have to blaze forward so fast that you know there\'s no hope left behind you—that hope lies only in what may come. And this is why you  try and befriend the giant lizards that creep around your walls. And it\'s also why you tell yourself that giant bug swarms flew into your house back home too.\r\n\r\nI had come here with the naive notion that I would somehow change my community for the better. No, when the score is finally tallied at the end of the game, it\'ll be sweet, capricious Thailand that\'s changed me far more than I\'d have ever dreamed of changing her.\r\n\r\nAnd even though I recognize this, even though I recognize that futility is in the augury of written stars, I\'m still hoping that my ambitions will return.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.weiluen.com/blog/assets/water-world_mg_0828_v2.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-55\" title=\"water-world_mg_0828_v2\" src=\"http://www.weiluen.com/blog/assets/water-world_mg_0828_v2.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"660\" height=\"440\" /></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Here, I\'m reminded of a pithy truth that I seem to have forgotten back home:  self-actualization is awfully hard when you\'re struggling to stay afloat.</p>\r\n<a href=\"http://www.weiluen.com/blog/assets/wale-ambition-copy.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-54\" title=\"wale-ambition-copy\" src=\"http://www.weiluen.com/blog/assets/wale-ambition-copy-600x600.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"600\" height=\"600\" /></a>', 'Ambition', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '32-revision-24', '', '', '2012-10-26 07:00:24', '2012-10-26 00:00:24', '', '32', 'http://www.weiluen.com/blog/219', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
