('222', '1', '2012-10-23 01:49:49', '2012-10-22 18:49:49', '&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.weiluen.com/blog/assets/DSC00167.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-medium wp-image-137\" title=\"DSC00167\" src=\"http://www.weiluen.com/blog/assets/DSC00167-400x300.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"400\" height=\"300\" /></a>\r\n\r\nI’ll take a cue from Humbert Humbert. You may hate my style, so sorry in advance.\r\n\r\nI’m a terrible sucker for melodrama, but there’s still something to be said about flying over an ocean: it’s not just time that changes; there’s a quiet moment for self-reflection; you can think clearly. You’re not here and you’re not there. Somewhere above the Pacific – or Atlantic – dwells a deep melancholy, where you can think in the most clear – and perhaps literal – sense of what you’re leaving behind and what you’re going towards.  And it’s probably natural to be apprehensive: I won’t be some vacationer looking in at a culture from afar. This is a move. I’ll be home soon. Loves, it’s seven hours to Tokyo.', 'The First of Many', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '13-revision-11', '', '', '2012-10-23 01:49:49', '2012-10-22 18:49:49', '', '13', 'http://www.weiluen.com/blog/222', '0', 'revision', '', '0'),
('224', '1', '2012-10-24 07:55:12', '2012-10-24 00:55:12', 'I\'ve been neglecting you. But where could I even begin? I\'ve taken a turn towards the taciturn—that definitely seems less funny now that it’s down in writing.  There’s just a friction to communication here. And that’s true of my Thailand writ large: I can’t talk to the other volunteers, I can’t talk to my host family, and I can’t talk to my friends back home. I feel stuck in the same purgatory that I felt on the plane ride over: I’m not here and I’m not there.', 'Foreign', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '22-revision-4', '', '', '2012-10-24 07:55:12', '2012-10-24 00:55:12', '', '22', 'http://www.weiluen.com/blog/224', '0', 'revision', '', '0'),
