 fragile wires keeping me from certain peril. But as long as my fan is spinning, I know that the combination of sweat—lovely imagery, I know—and scorching air being blown over my back will somehow eke out a win in favor of livable conditions. At least the sisters Fate seem to be enjoying their little dabble with irony: haha, thin wires are keeping my life in the balance, haha! &nbsp;I suppose, if the fan goes out, I can take a deep breath and soak in the&nbsp;bucolic&nbsp;milieu of rural Asia—you know, with only small hints of burning trash and PAHs floating through my lungs. Keep me in your thoughts; this week, as you might be able to tell from my histrionic tone, &nbsp;has been a bit rough.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h4><strong>On a Completely&nbsp;Unrelated&nbsp;Note About Organization . . . &nbsp;.&nbsp;</strong></h4>\r\nI told myself that I would start using <a title=\"Remember The Milk\" href=\"http://jh.weiluen.com/SjW86Z\">RTM</a>&nbsp;(remember the milk) to organize my life. It\'s been somewhat successful. My migration from the usual Google tasks isn\'t quite complete, but I\'m finding that the added plugins are highly beneficial, e.g., using <a title=\"YAR Plugin for RTM\" href=\"http://jh.weiluen.com/SjYCSM\" target=\"_blank\">YAR</a>, I\'m currently tracking the amount of time that I\'m spending on all of my activities; this lets me see a breakdown of my day in pie graph form. &nbsp;And if you\'re one of those <a title=\"Wiki Getting Things DOne\" href=\"http://jh.weiluen.com/SjYN0r\" target=\"_blank\">GTD</a> (Getting Things Done) fans, RTM is completely compatible. There are also some pretty sweet plugins that allow you to directly incorporate RTM into your Google apps, e.g., calendar and Gmail, too.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nSo yea, Tess,&nbsp;you might\'ve been right all along: maybe more structure is helpful?\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_316\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"400\"]<a style=\"color: #005580; text-decoration: underline;\" href=\"http://www.weiluen.com/blog/assets/2012-11-10-22.54.44.jpg\" rel=\"prettyPhoto\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-316\" title=\"Tweety Bird\" src=\"http://www.weiluen.com/blog/assets/2012-11-10-22.54.44-400x300.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></a> Tweety Bird[/caption]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nI\'ll leave you with a picture of an adorable bird that flew into my room. The bird\'s just been hanging out. Neat! I should probably get to work. . . .', 'The Heat Win!', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '303-revision-34', '', '', '2012-11-21 08:32:13', '2012-11-21 01:32:13', '', '303', 'http://www.weiluen.com/blog/368', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
